Example

Suppose you are interested in studying the relationships between fuel efficiency and other features of the automobile such as engine size, horsepower, weight and speed.

Software requirements

To participate in this brief coding walkthrough, please visit URL and download this repository.

  1. Click “Clone or Download” –> “Download Zip”; extract this file to Desktop.

(Git users should use git clone)

  1. Download R version 3.5.2

  2. Download RStudio Open Source License FREE

Run the installers and follow the instructions for both 2) and 3) above.

Load data

mt = read.csv("~/mtcars.csv")

# Print the data
# mt
